{"question_id": "Q002", "question": "How does Kachru's concentric circles model distinguish between the Inner, Outer, and Expanding circles?", "ground_truth": "The Inner circle refers to native speakers of English as a first language. The Outer circle refers to countries where English became an official second language, often through colonial history. The Expanding circle refers to places where English is mainly used as a foreign or international language.", "category": "direct_fact_lookup", "difficulty": "easy", "policy": "maddpg_no_ceb", "data_source": "live_llm", "final_status": "accepted", "final_answer": "I can't answer your question because it is unrelated to the provided documents. The documents appear to be about a Transformer model architecture, specifically describing the encoder and decoder layers. There is no mention of Kachru's concentric circles model.", "token_f1": 0.1493, "rouge_l": 0.1136, "correctness": 0.1493, "faithfulness": 0.6667, "citation_support": 0.6667, "source_precision": 0.0, "source_recall": 0.0, "verification_pass": 1, "unsupported_claims": 1, "latency_seconds": 62.5204, "num_llm_calls": 5, "token_usage": 3117, "num_steps": 7, "trace": [{"step": 1, "agent": "retriever", "action": "hybrid_rerank", "params": {"dense_sparse_weight": 0.5183956250548363, "top_k": 21, "rerank_threshold": 0.1781303882598877, "source_diversity": 0.43039678037166595}, "reward": -0.1228, "done": false}, {"step": 2, "agent": "grader", "action": "medium_filter", "params": {"relevance_threshold": 0.5362711250782013, "evidence_keep_ratio": 0.21162673830986023, "strictness_score": 0.6320505440235138}, "reward": -0.2884, "done": false}, {"step": 3, "agent": "generator", "action": "generate_with_strict_citations", "params": {"temperature": 0.250999391078949, "citation_strictness": 0.7311184853315353, "max_tokens": 856, "answer_detail_level": 0.461935643106699}, "reward": -0.3094, "done": false}, {"step": 4, "agent": "verifier", "action": "verify_answer", "params": {"su