{"question_id": "Q003", "question": "Why does the English paper argue that what English is depends on context?", "ground_truth": "The paper argues that English can refer to different things in different contexts, such as a people, a spoken language, a codified system in grammars and dictionaries, or literature, so its meaning depends on the setting in which it is discussed.", "category": "definition_explanation", "difficulty": "medium", "policy": "maddpg_no_ceb", "data_source": "live_llm", "final_status": "rejected", "final_answer": "The English paper argues that what English is depends on context because a school subject aims to develop a wide range of language and communicative skills for varying contexts and audiences.", "token_f1": 0.4127, "rouge_l": 0.25, "correctness": 0.4127, "faithfulness": 0.0, "citation_support": 0.0, "source_precision": 0.5, "source_recall": 1.0, "verification_pass": 0, "unsupported_claims": 1, "latency_seconds": 60.826, "num_llm_calls": 7, "token_usage": 2887, "num_steps": 10, "trace": [{"step": 1, "agent": "retriever", "action": "hybrid_rerank", "params": {"dense_sparse_weight": 0.48679533787071705, "top_k": 23, "rerank_threshold": 0.2651537358760834, "source_diversity": 0.3653858155012131}, "reward": -0.1121, "done": false}, {"step": 2, "agent": "grader", "action": "medium_filter", "params": {"relevance_threshold": 0.5187206342816353, "evidence_keep_ratio": 0.19252201914787292, "strictness_score": 0.6429399996995926}, "reward": -0.2696, "done": false}, {"step": 3, "agent": "generator", "action": "generate_with_strict_citations", "params": {"temperature": 0.21700650453567505, "citation_strictness": 0.7654826939105988, "max_tokens": 871, "answer_detail_level": 0.5139506412670016}, "reward": -0.2861, "done": false}, {"step": 4, "agent": "verifier", "action": "verify_answer", "params": {"support_threshold": 0.7098105698823929, "confidence_threshold": 0.5277772545814514}, "reward": -0.3166, "done": false}, {"step": 5, "agent": "verifier", "